Moody's Investors Service Inc said itdowngraded 50 mln dlrs of debt of Allied Bancshares Inc and thelead bank, Allied Bank of Texas.    Cut were the parent's senior debt to Ba-3 from Baa-2 andcommercial paper to Not Prime from Prime-2. The lead bank'slong-term deposits were reduced to Ba-1 from Baa-2 andshort-term deposits were cut to Not Prime from Prime-2.    Moody's cited the effects of a weak operating environmenton Allied's asset quality and profitability. The rating agencyexpects nonperforming loans to remain high by industrystandards because of exposure to energy and real estate. Reuter&#3;